I don't like the whole neurotypical vs neurodivervent mindset, it's just another us vs them system. Of course it feels good to belong to a group, def one that seems to be getting more recognition. Just, don't bully people for being different (or "normal"). Be nice to each other❤️

Also when I say it's not cool I'm not gatekeeping how people talk about their adhd. I make lots of self deprecating jokes about mine. I just feel like people now think it's a funny thing to have, or it's not serous. But it can be so debilitating, especially for the self employed.

A reminder that having adhd isn't "cool". It can make your life so difficult and make you feel like you're miles behind your peers. Adults with ADHD are 3x more likely to also have depression, and ADHD symptoms can get much worse before your monthly cycle (PMS/PMDD). It sucks.
